ABILITIES
Titan's Tithe (Reckless): The doubling enchantment works but the Echo uses it the way the player did ΓÇö it doesn't bank kills, it spends the x2 immediately on the next hit. It will never reach x4 on its own. If someone COACHES it to hold charges, it can learn. Slowly.
Spirit Form: Can pass through solid objects by concentrating (costs 4 FP). Cannot maintain solidity while doing so ΓÇö it's intangible for the duration. Useful for scouting, infiltration, and emotional devastation (walking through a closed door to sit beside someone who's grieving).
Fading: The Echo is sustained by the Aetherial Matrix's residual energy. Over time (weeks/months), this energy will deplete. The Echo will become more translucent, less solid, eventually unable to interact with the physical world. Finding a way to sustain the Echo permanently becomes a quest ΓÇö or the party watches their friend's ghost slowly disappear.
PERSONALITY
It IS Kyboh. Same jokes. Same loyalty. Same recklessness. Same heart. But there are cracks:
It doesn't need to eat, sleep, or breathe. It sometimes forgets to pretend.
It can't feel temperature. It doesn't shiver in the cold. It doesn't warm its hands by the fire. It sits by the fire because Kyboh would, and it takes a moment to realize it can't feel the heat.
It is slowly becoming aware that its memories might not be its own. Small inconsistencies. Moments where it reaches for something and its hand passes through. Moments where it says "I remember when I..." and then trails off, uncertain if the memory is real or recorded.
The existential question: If it has all of Kyboh's memories and personality, is it Kyboh? Or is it a very convincing recording? The party will have opinions. The Echo will have opinions. Neither set of opinions will be comfortable.

GM NOTES
Hjolmar-Kyboh is the scariest villain in the campaign because the party built him. Every session they spent helping Kyboh ΓÇö the Anchor, the Matrix quest, the Mzinchaleft dungeon ΓÇö was a session delivering resources to their enemy. The power-ups they earned for their friend are now the weapons being used against them.
The Echo Mimic is the most emotionally complex NPC because it doesn't know what it is. Playing the Echo means playing someone who genuinely believes they are a person, slowly discovering they might be a copy. Handle this with care. The comedy of Kyboh's personality will make the horror of his situation worse, not better.
The player's waste is the villain's gain. Hjolmar uses every mechanic the player ignored. The doubling enchantment, banked and timed. The Oversoul, mastered and efficient. The aetherial mutation, fully understood. Every time Hjolmar-Kyboh does something devastating with a power the player never bothered to learn, the table will feel it.
The Fading mechanic is a clock. The Echo is temporary unless the party finds a solution. This creates urgency without combat ΓÇö the spirit of their friend is slowly becoming less real. Every session it gets a little more translucent. The quest to save it is a race against dissolution.
Track GEAR's knowledge. GEAR knows Hjolmar. GEAR knows the Aetherial Matrix. GEAR knows consciousness transfer technology. GEAR can explain exactly what happened to Kyboh if anyone asks the right questions. He is the key to understanding the enemy and potentially the key to reversing what was done.

